- Triglyceride storage and glucose metabolism (insulin and glucagon receptors)
- Secretion of many bioactive molecules: leptin (regulates satiety) angiotensinogen (blood pressure) steroids (glucocorticoids \& sex hormones) growth factors (e.g. insulin-like growth factor, tumor necrosis factor $\alpha$ ) cytokines (e.g. interleukin-6)
