\section*{Billiary tree}
- The system is lined by cholangiocytes
- Bile contains both organic components like lecithin, cholesterol and bilirubin and inorganic components (bile salts).
- The bile produced by the hepatocyte flows through the bile canaliculi, bile ductules, and bile ducts.
- The common hepatic duct, after receiving the cystic duct from the gallbladder, continues to the duodenum as the common bile duct (ductus choledochus).
